In the frames of the internship different insights to the information management processes are provided. Students have opportunity to observe the professional work of information specialist in real work situation. At the end of the internship, students are required to submit internship report, where the specific features of information management in different organizations are analyzed and acquired knowledge and experience during the internship is reflected.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The purpose of the internship is to get acquainted with different aspects of the work of the information specialist in multiple institutional and thematic settings.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  On completion of the course, students: - have primary knowledge about the tasks the information specialists perform in their professional work  and are able to draw parallels between the studies and further professional career as information specialist; - can analyze and compare specific features of information work of different organizations and the role of the information specialist; - have got an overview about information processes of the organizations and is able to assess the functionality of these processes.
